The paper deals with the Planar Steiner Tree problem, which is a fundamental problem in network design and graph theory. The problem involves finding a subtree of a graph that connects a subset of vertices (terminals) with minimum weight. The paper proposes a new algorithm for this problem that has a running time of $2^{O(k)} n^{O(\sqrt{k})}$ and uses only polynomial space. The problem is specific to planar graphs and involves terminals that can be covered by the boundary of a small number of faces. Therefore, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
